title: * Re: Gun faulted on peak power interlock
text: Talked to Ryan and he said the reset button works now. To get it to reset we had to turn off the slow feedback, drop the ADES on the fast feedback to 5.0 and turn off the fast feedback. Then we were able to reset it. After that we re-enabled the fast feedback and walked the ADES back up to 40. After confirming that the WVG Power readback on the slow feedback was reading ~10 MW, we re-enabled the slow feedback. If 10-2 trips on peak power interlock again over the weekend, you can try these steps to reset it, but if it trips again shortly after we should just leave it off.

title: 22-3 WVG. Howard out to juice filament.
HXR Optics Fast Fault 1. XCS was not aware. They are going to acknowledge.
* Re: 22-3 WVG probably needs local filament juice. Flaky gauge?
text: Did recover okay, but the response was not as I expected. Locally gauge controller indicated that it was asleep (Lo in the Lo scale). Juicing filament for a moment would get some response, but not much. Holding the filament button down for a few seconds would get the pressure readout to increase somewhat, and the station would come on. But as soon as the button was released the readout would drop and the station would again trip. Never saw above ~8e-9 torr doing this. Decided to hold the filament down for a long time. Pressure readout slowly increased in the e-9 scale, but again as soon as filament was released the readout would again drop and the station would trip off. Eventually while doing this, at one point the pressure shot up into the high e-8 scale. Then after releasing the filament button, the pressure stayed in that range (station happily running) and slowly started to decrease.

title: 26-4: PFN Tuning CATER 154372
text: Got permission from ACR to try and tune the PFN cold. Readjusted straps to match what was done to 10-2 and 10-3, and it worked. Got slope from from -1.7 to 0.4. Strap pattern is 1-3, 2-6, 3-8, 4-7, 5-7, 6-8, 7-5 and 8-3. ct

title: State of Modulators and possibility of 15 GeV tomorrow
text: Following stations are down: 22-7 (EMC) 23-6 (WKL) 28-2 (MNT, problem with waveguide gauge) 30-3 (KMC) 26-3 has not been usable for a while, not exactly sure why aside from fallout from MR upgrade. Critt tells me that 28-2 needs vacuum shop, unlikely to be fixed by tomorrow. Fixing 30-3 required taking down two sectors of RF to apply LOTO and is a big job, not doable by tomorrow. The remaining stations should be fixable, aside from 26-3. Does this get us to 15 GeV? 6*8 - 3 = 45 stations. Avg 225 MeV Egain per station gives max L3 Egain of 10125. If we raise BC2 to 5.2 GeV, we can make it to 15 GeV with 1 station's worth of headroom. Since we should have all L2 stations available, this is doable.
